name: Nico Collins injury
summary: Houston Texans wide receiver Nico Collins has been placed on injured reserve with a hamstring injury. The injury occurred during the team's second quarter against the Buffalo Bills, forcing Collins to leave the game early. The Texans have designated Collins as "week-to-week," meaning he will miss at least the next four games. The injury is a significant setback for the Texans, who are already struggling with a depleted receiving corps. Collins had emerged as a reliable target for quarterback Davis Mills in recent weeks, and his absence will create a major void in the offense. The Texans will need other receivers to step up in Collins' absence, such as Brandin Cooks, Chris Moore, and Phillip Dorsett.

summary: Republican Congresswoman Marjorie Taylor Greene has faced widespread condemnation for her unsubstantiated claims that Democrats or other unspecified entities have the ability to control the weather. Despite widespread criticism from both sides of the political spectrum, Greene has defended her remarks, suggesting that weather manipulation is possible and that there is evidence to support her claims. The allegations have been dismissed as baseless conspiracy theories by the Biden administration, and have also raised concerns about the increasing prevalence of misinformation and the erosion of trust in public discourse.

name: Ethel Kennedy
summary: Ethel Kennedy, the widow of Robert F. Kennedy and matriarch of the Kennedy family, has been hospitalized after suffering a stroke. The 96-year-old was admitted to a hospital in Washington, D.C., according to a statement from her family. The stroke is reported to have occurred on Tuesday, and Kennedy is currently being treated in the intensive care unit. Her family reports that she is surrounded by family and friends, and doctors are monitoring her condition. Kennedy is the last surviving member of the family's younger generation and has been a prominent figure in the family's history and politics for decades. She is known for her work in human rights advocacy and has been involved in numerous charitable organizations.

name: Aaron Pierre
summary: HBO's upcoming DC series "Lanterns" has cast Aaron Pierre as John Stewart, the iconic Green Lantern. This marks the first time Stewart will lead a live-action DC project, serving as the third incarnation of the Green Lantern alongside Kyle Chandler's Hal Jordan. Pierre's casting, coming just a month after his breakout role in "Rebel Ridge," is significant for the DC Universe (DCU). It follows the recent confirmation of Finn Wittrock as Guy Gardner and Jeremy Irvine as Alan Scott in the DCU's Green Lantern franchise. name: David Baker
summary: The 2024 Nobel Prize in Chemistry has been awarded to three scientists, including University of Washington biochemist David Baker. Baker, a UC Berkeley alumnus, was recognized for his groundbreaking work in protein design using artificial intelligence. His research has led to advances in fields such as medicine, biotechnology, and materials science. The prize also honors two other scientists for their contributions to protein chemistry: John Jumper and Demis Hassabis of DeepMind Technologies. Their work has enabled the development of powerful AI tools that can predict and design protein structures, paving the way for new treatments and therapies.

name: Port St. Lucie
summary: As Hurricane Milton approaches, Port St. Lucie has issued a precautionary boil water notice and is preparing for potential flooding. The city's Emergency Operations Center is active, and residents are advised to "prepare" and "be safe" in anticipation of hurricane-strength winds and flooding. At least 20 homes have already been damaged due to reported tornadoes, and law enforcement has closed a road due to heavy flooding affecting two counties. Port St. Lucie is urging residents to stay informed and take necessary precautions, including stocking up on supplies and preparing evacuation plans.
